<subSubSection id="6E586A8729F4C9D7B5AB7BED6DBCCCB5" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="FC40853CBA4E33534FFD76B5D96803D5" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="24553C85C544B27155326AA0FFE58A9F" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">
Restricted to Argentina, Paraguay and Brazil (states of 
<normalizedToken id="C0026ABB7E14F6E8B5BC4E5A52F56A55" originalValue="Ceará">Ceara</normalizedToken>
, Mato Grosso and Mato Grosso do Sul).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="16DC2B57E43349BED3BE4DF2E552F53E" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" type="nomenclatural notes">
<paragraph id="7A1DD61505EE6D91252617C68E895E6F" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Nomenclatural notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5DD93F432EECF43F69C51F1844402DA4" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">
<bibRefCitation id="3E97421EF296B77FBAE48A3F1DB800EB" author="Schulz, AG" journalOrPublisher="Darwiniana" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" pagination="45 - 87" refId="B95" refString="Schulz, AG, 1942. Las Pontederiaceas de la Argentina. Darwiniana 6 (1): 45 - 87" title="Las Pontederiaceas de la Argentina." volume="6" year="1942">Schulz (1942)</bibRefCitation>
, when describing his new 
<taxonomicName id="B5C6183C12A49C055022D3D9E0070F80" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="E." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="E. meyeri" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="meyeri">
<emphasis id="9FADA61292963C8EF494D409A7E29119" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">E. meyeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, cites two specimens from the same collection, one housed at SI and another at GH. Furthermore, a third specimen, housed at LIL was found by us. After carefully analysing the syntypes, we noticed that the specimen at SI perfectly matches the original illustration. Furthermore, it is widely known that Schulz worked at the Instituto de 
<normalizedToken id="7A0D367A8DD21D8130F0068E0053A8FE" originalValue="Botánica">Botanica</normalizedToken>
Darwinion, thus, making the specimen at SI the obvious choice of a lectotype.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FFC770C4B5D6267F1EE5D64823773EEB" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" type="taxonomical notes">
<paragraph id="7808FF0759002470ABAA7BD11BE22043" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Taxonomical notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="53EB3F7B3111F257865E55B4935F1C41" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">
Current databases (
<bibRefCitation id="615FB24A22ABC7DFEED0E74D994954BE" author="eMonocot" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" publicationUrl="http://e-monocot.org" refId="B29" refString="eMonocot, 2010. eMonocot (Version 1.0.2). http://e-monocot.org" title="eMonocot (Version 1.0.2)." url="http://e-monocot.org" year="2010">eMonocot 2010</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="474E33B60A802E9B6A42277E09F5CE7F" author="The Plant List" journalOrPublisher="Mathematical Biosciences" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" publicationUrl="http://www.theplantlist.org" refId="B114" refString="The Plant List, 2013. The Plant List (Version 1.1). http://www.theplantlist.org" title="The Plant List (Version 1.1)." url="http://www.theplantlist.org" year="2013">The Plant List 2013</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="B0610D51E152AF3D1776653FE69F8D6A" author="Govaerts, R" journalOrPublisher="Hindasia Publishers, Delhi" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" publicationUrl="http://wcsp.science.kew.org/" refId="B40" refString="Govaerts, R, 2018. World Checklist of Pontederiaceae. Facilitated by the Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew. http://wcsp.science.kew.org/" title="World Checklist of Pontederiaceae. Facilitated by the Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew." url="http://wcsp.science.kew.org/" year="2018">Govaerts 2018</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="E794FF241B0082055B07AE9EB6DF666D" author="Tropicos. org" journalOrPublisher="Mathematical Biosciences" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" publicationUrl="http://www.tropicos.org/" refId="B116" refString="Tropicos.org, 2018. Tropicos. Missouri Botanical Garden. http://www.tropicos.org/" title="Tropicos. Missouri Botanical Garden." url="http://www.tropicos.org/" year="2018">Tropicos.org 2018</bibRefCitation>
) have treated 
<taxonomicName id="039D25CD2DAD7762A1223F3980BF5C1C" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="E." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="E. meyeri" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="meyeri">
<emphasis id="F9FDBAE8CFDC3A3628DE655AB1083D52" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">E. meyeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(≡ 
<taxonomicName id="0AB2E0C9477325353AB77073427FA823" family="Pontederiaceae" genus="P." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. meyeri" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="meyeri">
<emphasis id="2D6793DC67C391266742C2C0ECC6F688" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">P. meyeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="A5ABB45DB5EBB3D57F2F5A7129A1B289" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="E." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="E. paniculata" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="paniculata">
<emphasis id="D0028F7F4AC530D2637E0424ED413D51" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">E. paniculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(≡ 
<taxonomicName id="F175CFB7FC335AD63323D4F910AF3702" family="Pontederiaceae" genus="P." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. paniculata" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="paniculata">
<emphasis id="3FAA17144A69C052EAF8C310F1A7AE7D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">P. paniculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Nonetheless, as indicated in our identification key and by 
<bibRefCitation id="BEE97D934D30CE36707A9E5963BA5062" author="Horn, CN" journalOrPublisher="Candollea" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" pagination="127 - 130" refId="B55" refString="Horn, CN, 1998. Notulae ad Floram Paraguaiensem 66: A note on Eichhornia paniculata (Spreng.) Solms and Eichhornia meyeri A.G.Schulz (Pontederiaceae) in Paraguay. Candollea 53: 127 - 130" title="Notulae ad Floram Paraguaiensem 66: A note on Eichhornia paniculata (Spreng.) Solms and Eichhornia meyeri A. G. Schulz (Pontederiaceae) in Paraguay." volume="53" year="1998">Horn (1998)</bibRefCitation>
, both species are distinct, being easily differentiated in the field and herbaria. Thus, 
<taxonomicName id="A520F242349FD9EDCD560B7EBDD7B7C7" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="E." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="E. meyeri" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="meyeri">
<emphasis id="E0165C6021343785D73B925D0CCABE75" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">E. meyeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is here re-established and transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="68D17FDBB1E7734E57264F9A50B2245A" authorityName="subg. Cabanisia (Klotzsch ex Schltdl.) M. Pell. &amp; C. N. Horn" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="subg. Cabanisia (Klotzsch ex Schltdl.) M. Pell. &amp; C. N. Horn" baseAuthorityYear="2018" class="Liliopsida" family="Commelinaceae" genus="Pontederia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pontederia" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D1481BCAE53B6404A2A82530CDE61473" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Pontederia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="44DE4AA084060476FAE996CD70444DF6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">s.l.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
